content: Does what it's meant to do. While visually having more than one alien blip is pretty cool on the tracker.. You can easily "control" the distance when you set it to 1 on both speed and number. Gives the "moving about" feel more natural, also gives you more control as to how fast the blip moves to the center. You'd have to tap in between pulses to not "cut" the blip sound. Just my two cents if adding the noise when playing the Alien RPG.

Sounds are great but the alien dots images don't appear on my screen and the range and distance graph lines are also not showing on my screen..please help...I use to have this ap on another phone and the ap worked great... idk why not on this phone..
Landscape mode only. Range graph rotates, but in the wrong direction when you turn your phone. I'm using pixel 3a. No exit button.

For everyone who can't get the aliens to appear when they tap- Click the tiny config button on the lower right and adjust the settings. Once you do that, the aliens will appear when you tap the screen. Works great. Should look perfect in my 3d printed motion tracker.
Thank you so very much this app...

The app loads and looks good but when I tap the screen no dots appear. So at least right now it does not do what I need. Planned to use this as part of a tabletop game and I need the sound for a target approaching.

Really good app! Sounds are on point, spin is a bit fast, menu options are well hidden. Wish you could set a point and walk toward it and have distance count down. Right now the point(s) move toward you only.
I tap the screen, the dots dont appear!
Rotation direction is backwards and no app icon
